everybody who needs prescription

17:24.433 --> 17:26.933 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
drugs.

17:26.933 --> 17:29.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEPHEN UBL: Well,
again, our sector may
be a little bit lagging
other health care sectors

17:29.800 --> 17:34.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in this movement towards paying
based on value, as opposed to
the volume of care, but it's

17:36.466 --> 17:39.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
one of the rare areas
in health care policy
where everyone agrees.

17:39.000 --> 17:43.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Payers want to move
in this direction, our
members want to move in
this direction, providers

17:43.266 --> 17:45.266 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
want to move in this direction.

17:45.266 --> 17:47.666 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Again, take cancer therapy.

17:47.666 --> 17:50.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We want to be able to
offer novel discounts.

17:50.633 --> 17:54.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But there's a number of
public policy barriers
that stand in the way of
moving in that direction.

17:54.400 --> 17:59.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: One of
