facilities, state and
local governments.

20:13.633 --> 20:18.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, for our part, we're
committed to engaging with
all those stakeholders
to find solutions.

20:20.266 --> 20:22.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And is
there going to be a
change, do you think?

20:22.366 --> 20:26.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STEPHEN UBL: Well, just to give
you an example, the industry is
in favor of mandatory training

20:28.600 --> 20:31.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for health care professionals
to learn more about pain
management, to learn more about

20:31.033 --> 20:33.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
appropriate prescribing.

20:33.633 --> 20:36.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So we want to be part of the
solution to this problem.

20:36.166 --> 20:40.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Stephen Ubl,
pharmaceutical manufacturers
association, thank you very

20:40.600 --> 20:41.600 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
much.

20:41.600 --> 20:42.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
STEPHEN UBL: Thank you.

20:42.600 --> 20:44.666 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's great to be with you.

20:44.666 --> 20:48.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Some of the
most influential figures in
health care are here in Aspen,

